import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['open'] = pd.to_numeric(data['open'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['open'])]
    sns.distplot(data['open'], kde=False, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['open'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['open'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Opening Prices')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of daily opening prices?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='close', data=data, color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the trend of daily closing prices over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Closing Price')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="darkgrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.distplot(data['high'], kde=False, color='blue', ax=ax)
    ax.axvline(data['high'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    ax.axvline(data['high'].median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label='Median')
    ax.set_xlabel('High Prices')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of daily high prices?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
